content:
Assuming this is the result of the Name vs Title thing is being enforced (as announced earlier)

rg.hl7.fhir.exceptions.FHIRException: Cannot generate Java code for profile http://fhir.org/guides/argonaut-scheduling/StructureDefinition/argo-appt because the name "Argonaut Appointment Profile" is not a valid Java class name

No, it's just a new thing Grahame spits out. If you disable "java" as an output, the message will go away. That said, yes this is something we'll need to fix. (I need to know how to have both a Title and a name in spreadsheets before I can fix some of mine.)
I have given up on the spreadsheets due to parser errors and because don't have time to debug. Made the leap to Forge
